Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:14 PM (64-06) Defendant Charles G Kummerow Jr. appeared by video.  Attorney Larry R Pruden in court for Charles G Kummerow Jr.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin by ADA Herrmann in court. 
State called to the stand as a witness, Officer Matthew Boney.
Matthew Boney duly sworn by the clerk and testified on direct examination by ADA Herrmann. 
Witness has identified the defendant on the video in court. Exhibit #1, Criminal Complaint and Amended Complaint  marked, identified and discussed.
Attorney Pruden is objecting to the receipt of Exhibits.
Requesting Court take judicial notice of file 19CF571. Objection by Attorney Pruden. Court will take judicial notice of file 19CF571.
Exhibit #1 offered and received by the Court.
2:29PM - Argument by the State, requesting bindover.
Defense requesting dismissal.
Court finds probable cause that a felony has been committed and that the defendant likely committed it and binds him over to stand trial on the charges.
Arraignment held in open court.
Attorney Pruden acknowledged receipt of the Information, waived reading and plead not guilty to all charges on behalf of his client.
Speedy Trial reserved.

Adj. 2:32PM

BOND TO COVER 22CF521 & 19CF571

NO USE OF ANYTHING WITH INTERNET ACCESS. 
Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant is to be booked and printed within twenty-four (24) hours. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S):NO CONTACT WITH MINORS.  Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.
